data.name: SystemDependent
desc: These constants are used to specify systems which depend on return values.
You should avoid system-dependent methods if possible.
The Symbols are now prepended with SYSTEM_ thus we avoid collisions with system headers.

items.name: SYSTEM_WIN32
lines: The called interface method returns a value specified for Windows.
These are Windows XP or higher.

items.name: SYSTEM_WIN16
lines: The called interface method returns a value specified for 16-bit Windows.

items.name: SYSTEM_JAVA
lines: The called interface method returns a value specified for Java.
These are JRE 1.1, JRE 1.2, JDK 1.1, JDK 1.2 or higher.
The return should be a handle to a Java object locked with the call JavaEnvironment->NewGlobalRef( ... ) by the callee.

items.name: SYSTEM_OS2
lines: The called interface method returns a value specified for OS/2.

items.name: SYSTEM_MAC
lines: The called interface method returns a value specified for macOS.

items.name: SYSTEM_XWINDOW
lines: The called interface method returns a value specified for the X Window System.

items.name: SYSTEM_IOS
lines: The called interface method returns a value specified for iOS.

items.name: SYSTEM_ANDROID
lines: The called interface method returns a value specified for Android.
